data.text:
Moreover, in 2013, he played a very exceptional role in a comedy and drama-based short story in which he was showcased only for one episode along with Maki Horikita, Nanami Sakuraba, Takumi Saitoh, Shôtarô Mamiya, and Yû Koyanagi. Again in 2018, Keisuke portrayed the role of Black Woz in a popular animated t.v series named Kamen Rider Zi-O, which was directed in a action, adventure, and comedy based genres. Then in 2019, he received a huge opportunity to be cast in a few movies and series like Semiotoko a comedy-based series where he played the role of Kimura, along with Ryôsuke Yamada, Mio Imada, Haruka Kinami, Kô Takasugi, etc. An Incurable Case of Love is a romance and comedy-based series in which he played the role of Ryusei Nishi. In the same year, he played a vital role in his self-titled mini-series named Takeru No Plan Drive by sharing the stage with Ryûnosuke Kamiki and Takeru Satoh.

Keisuke Watanabe Kamen Rider Heisei Generations Forever

On the 22nd of December 2018, the movie Kamen Rider Heisei Generations Forever was released in which Keisuke performed the role of Woz which was very much loved by the critics and audiences. Further in the movie Kaisuke was signed along with some popular actors like So Okuno, Atsuhiro Inukai, Kôhei Takeda, Kaho Takada, and Hiroaki Nakagawa. The direction of the movie was given to Kyohei Yamaguchi and Kento Shimoyama one of the highest-paid animated directors in Japan. Basically, the movie was based on the genres of Action, Adventure, and Fantasy with the narration of companions who lost their memory due to evil enemies.
